      <abstract>
        <p>Television ratings for NHL Stanley Cup playoffs discussed (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Devils' 3-1 victory over Dallas in Game 4 of the Stanley Cup finals Monday night generated a 3.3 Nielsen rating on ABC, the same rating Fox received last season for its second finals broadcast.</p>
        <p>ABC's first game on Saturday rated a 2.3, down from Fox's 3.4.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Devils' 3-1 victory over Dallas in Game 4 of the Stanley Cup finals Monday night generated a 3.3 Nielsen rating on ABC, the same rating Fox received last season for its second finals broadcast.</p>
        <p>ABC's first game on Saturday rated a 2.3, down from Fox's 3.4.</p>
        <p>Through two games, ABC is averaging a 2.8 rating, down from Fox's 3.4. One ratings point represents about 1.01 million TV households.</p>
        <p>ABC will carry the remaining games of the finals, including tomorrow night's Game 5 from Continental Arena in East Rutherford, N.J.</p>
        <p>ESPN, which carried Games 1 and 2, posted an average 1.95 cable rating, down 28 percent from a 2.7 for Games 3 and 4 of the Buffalo-Dallas finals last year. Each cable ratings point equals about 760,000 households.</p>
        <p>RICHARD SANDOMIR</p>
        <p>N.H.L.</p>
      </block>
